[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software requirements specification
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Software Requirements Specification (SRS) phase
for the software element of the railway control and protection system
identified below. It is prepared in accordance with EN 50716:2023,
Clause 7.2 (Software requirements), and collects three output deliverables
from Table A.1:

  6. Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
  7. Overall Software Test Specification
  8. Software Requirements Verification Report

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 values (BASIC=HR, SIL_1–4=HR) for document-level requirements
  (docs 6 and 7) and technique requirements classified as HR.
- Table A.1 values (BASIC=R, SIL_1–4=HR) for verification report
  requirements (doc 8).
- Table A.2 values (BASIC=R, SIL_1=R, SIL_2=R, SIL_3=HR, SIL_4=HR) for
  specification techniques: modelling, structured methodology, decision tables.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: SRS-xxx.
- Replace every <...> placeholder with project-specific content.
- SRS-020 and SRS-021 are sample functional requirement entries; duplicate
  as needed for each software function and remove placeholders.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

