[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software requirements specification

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Requirements Specification (SRS) as
required by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.2. The SRS defines all functional,
interface, performance, and constraint requirements on the software item,
derived from system-level requirements and the operating environment.

The SRS is the primary input to the Software Architecture Specification
and to the Overall Software Test Specification (section 3 of this document).
<<<

