The safety integrity level applicable to this software item is: SIL <n>.

The SIL has been derived from the system hazard and risk analysis in
accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 4 (system level) and is documented
in: <Reference to system RAMS / hazard analysis document>.

The following software components are classified at the stated SIL:
  - <Component / module name>: SIL <n>
  - <Component / module name>: Non-safety (SIL 0)

Non-safety components that interface with safety components shall be treated
as potential sources of common cause failure and shall be subject to the
interface requirements in section 2.3.
