[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Interface requirements

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-030
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software/hardware interface requirements
STATEMENT: >>>
The software shall interface with the following hardware components.
Each interface shall be fully specified including signal types, electrical
characteristics, timing, and error handling.

  Interface     | HW component         | Type        | Protocol / standard
  --------------|----------------------|-------------|---------------------
  <IF-HW-01>    | <e.g. CPU watchdog>  | Digital out | <WDT register write>
  <IF-HW-02>    | <e.g. I/O module>    | Digital I/O | <e.g. SPI, I²C>
  <IF-HW-03>    | <e.g. NV memory>     | R/W         | <e.g. SPI flash>
  <IF-HW-04>    | <e.g. comms ASIC>    | Serial      | <e.g. UART>

For each interface, the software shall:
  a) Initialise the hardware before use and verify correct initialisation.
  b) Detect and report communication faults within <n> ms.
  c) Apply the defined safe state on detected hardware failure.
  d) Handle all error responses defined in the hardware specification.

Hardware specification reference: <document ID>
<<<
