[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-031
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software/software interface requirements
STATEMENT: >>>
The software item shall exchange data with the following software components
or tasks. All interfaces shall be defined in terms of data structure, timing,
and error handling.

  Interface     | Remote SW component  | Direction   | Data / protocol
  --------------|----------------------|-------------|---------------------
  <IF-SW-01>    | <Vital kernel>       | Bidirect.   | <Shared memory / API>
  <IF-SW-02>    | <Diagnostics module> | Output      | <Log record struct>
  <IF-SW-03>    | <Comms driver>       | Bidirect.   | <Message queue>

For safety-critical inter-component interfaces:
  a) Data consistency shall be guaranteed (e.g. by mutual exclusion or
     double-buffer mechanisms).
  b) Stale or missing data shall be detected and handled within <n> ms.
  c) The API contract (preconditions, postconditions) shall be formally
     specified or verified by the supplier of each component.
<<<
