[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-032
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: External interface requirements
STATEMENT: >>>
The software shall communicate with the following external systems via
defined communication links.

  Interface     | External system         | Protocol            | SIL/safety
  --------------|-------------------------|---------------------|------------
  <IF-EXT-01>   | <Control centre>        | <e.g. IEC 60870-5>  | Non-safety
  <IF-EXT-02>   | <Adjacent interlocking> | <e.g. RSSP-I>       | SIL <n>
  <IF-EXT-03>   | <Train detection>       | <e.g. proprietary>  | SIL <n>

For safety-critical external interfaces, the software shall:
  a) Implement the error-detection and error-correction mechanisms defined
     by the applicable communication protocol standard.
  b) Detect loss of communication within <n> ms and apply the defined
     safe state.
  c) Authenticate the source of safety-critical messages (if required by
     the protocol or by the hazard analysis).

Communication protocol specifications: <document IDs>
<<<
