[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Requirements specification methods

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-060
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requirements modelling
STATEMENT: >>>
Formal or semi-formal modelling shall be used to describe the functional
behaviour of safety-related requirements where textual description alone
is insufficient for unambiguous specification. Applicable modelling
notations include:

  - State machines (e.g. UML state charts, SDL)
  - Data flow diagrams
  - Petri nets or timed automata (for timing-critical behaviour)
  - <Project-specific modelling notation>

Models shall be:
  a) Consistent with the textual requirements in this specification.
  b) Subject to the same document control as the SRS.
  c) Verified against system-level requirements (SRS-063).
  d) Traceable to the design elements they constrain.

Modelling tool: <tool name and version>
<<<
