[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-061
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Structured specification methodology
STATEMENT: >>>
A structured methodology shall be applied to the derivation and
organisation of software requirements from system-level inputs. The
methodology shall ensure:

  a) Systematic decomposition of system functions into software functions.
  b) Identification and explicit documentation of all safety-related
     requirements as distinct from non-safety requirements.
  c) Consistency checks between requirements at each decomposition level.
  d) Review of requirements for completeness, testability, and
     freedom from ambiguity before baseline.

Methodology applied: <e.g. SADT / IDEF0 / structured analysis / EARS>
Reference: <methodology document or standard>
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: R
SIL_2: R
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.2 – Structured methodology.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-062
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Decision tables for complex logic
STATEMENT: >>>
Decision tables shall be used to specify functional behaviour wherever
multiple input conditions determine the output, to ensure completeness
and freedom from ambiguity. Decision tables shall:

  a) Cover all combinations of input conditions relevant to safety.
  b) Specify the required output or action for each combination.
  c) Explicitly address the "don't care" and default cases.
  d) Be reviewed for consistency and completeness before baseline.

Decision tables form part of the SRS baseline and shall be subject to
the same version control and verification as the textual requirements.

Example table structure:
  Condition 1 | Condition 2 | Condition 3 | Required output
  ------------|-------------|-------------|------------------
  True        | True        | Any         | <output A>
  True        | False       | True        | <output B>
  ...         | ...         | ...         | ...
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: R
SIL_2: R
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.2 – Decision tables.

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Requirements verification method

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-063
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requirements verification approach
STATEMENT: >>>
All software requirements in this specification shall be verified against
the system-level requirements in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.2,
and the Software Verification Plan (SP-070). Verification shall confirm:

  a) Completeness: all system safety functions have been addressed in the SRS.
  b) Consistency: no conflicting requirements exist within the SRS or between
     the SRS and the system-level specification.
  c) Correctness: each requirement accurately reflects the system-level intent.
  d) Testability: each requirement can be verified by inspection, analysis,
     simulation, or test (as specified in the VERIFICATION_METHOD field).
  e) Traceability: each SRS requirement traces to at least one system
     requirement and to at least one test case in the Overall Software
     Test Specification (section 3).

Verification shall be conducted using the techniques specified in SRS-060
through SRS-062, and formally reviewed by the Software Verifier (SP-021)
before the SRS is baselined.

Verification report reference: section 4 of this document (SRS-080, SRS-081).
<<<
