[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Overall software test specification

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Overall Software Test Specification as required
by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.2 and Table A.1 (document 7). The test specification
defines the strategy, environment, and coverage objectives for testing the
software against the requirements of section 2. Detailed test cases are recorded
in individual test records and referenced from the Software Validation Report.
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Test strategy and scope

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-070
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software test strategy
STATEMENT: >>>
The software test strategy for this project comprises four test levels,
executed in the order stated:

  Level 1 – Software component testing (unit testing):
    Scope: individual software components / modules.
    Objective: verify each component against its component specification.
    Technique: structural testing (coverage objectives per SRS-073).
    Responsibility: <Software Developer / Verifier>.

  Level 2 – Software integration testing:
    Scope: integrated software modules on host or target.
    Objective: verify correct interaction between components and with
    the software/hardware interface (SRS-030, SRS-031).
    Technique: interface testing, error injection.
    Responsibility: <Software Verifier>.

  Level 3 – Software/hardware integration testing:
    Scope: integrated software on target hardware.
    Objective: verify software behaviour in the hardware environment,
    including timing (SRS-040, SRS-041) and HW interfaces (SRS-030).
    Technique: functional testing, timing measurement.
    Responsibility: <Software Verifier>.

  Level 4 – Software validation testing (overall software testing):
    Scope: complete software item on target or representative environment.
    Objective: verify all SRS requirements (section 2) are satisfied.
    Technique: black-box functional testing, requirements-based testing.
    Responsibility: <Software Validator (SP-081)>.

Exit criteria for each level shall be defined in the corresponding test
specification and reported in the phase verification report.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.2 and Table A.1, doc 7 – Overall software test specification.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-071
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Test scope and requirements traceability
STATEMENT: >>>
The test scope shall cover all software requirements specified in section 2
of this document. A requirements-to-test traceability matrix shall be
maintained and shall demonstrate:

  a) Every functional requirement (SRS-020 series) is addressed by at
     least one test case at Level 4 (validation testing).
  b) Every interface requirement (SRS-030 series) is addressed by at
     least one test case at Level 2 or Level 3.
  c) Every performance and timing requirement (SRS-040 series) is addressed
     by at least one measurement at Level 3 or Level 4.
  d) Traceability from each test case back to the requirement(s) it verifies.

Requirements not covered by dynamic testing shall be verified by analysis
or inspection, with the method and rationale recorded in the traceability
matrix.

Traceability matrix location: <document ID or tool reference>
<<<
