[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Test coverage objectives

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-073
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Test coverage objectives
STATEMENT: >>>
Structural test coverage shall be measured for all safety-related software
components and shall meet the following minimum objectives, in accordance
with EN 50716:2023, Table A.21:

  SIL 1:  Statement coverage (SC): 100 % of executable statements.
  SIL 2:  Branch coverage (BC): 100 % of branches (decision coverage).
  SIL 3:  Branch coverage (BC): 100 %; Modified Condition / Decision
          Coverage (MC/DC): HR – apply to safety-critical modules.
  SIL 4:  MC/DC: 100 % of safety-critical modules.

In addition, requirements-based test coverage shall demonstrate that every
software requirement in section 2 is exercised by at least one test case
at Level 4 (SRS-071).

Coverage measurement tool: <tool name and version – subject to tool
qualification per SP-082>

Residual coverage gaps (statements / branches not achievable by dynamic
test) shall be justified and supplemented by static analysis or inspection,
with evidence recorded in the Software Validation Report.
<<<
