[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Requirements Verification Report as
required by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.2 and Table A.1 (document 8). It records
the outcome of the independent verification of the Software Requirements
Specification (section 2) and the Overall Software Test Specification
(section 3) before those documents are baselined.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-080
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification scope and method
STATEMENT: >>>
The verification of the SRS and the Overall Software Test Specification
shall cover:

  a) Compliance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.2 requirements.
  b) Completeness and correctness of all requirements in section 2 relative
     to the system-level specification (<System SRS reference>).
  c) Internal consistency of the SRS: no conflicting or duplicate requirements.
  d) Adequacy of interface definitions (SRS-030 to SRS-032).
  e) Correctness of the modelling and decision tables (SRS-060 to SRS-062).
  f) Completeness and adequacy of the test strategy and coverage objectives
     (SRS-070 to SRS-073): every SRS requirement has at least one test case.
  g) Adequacy of independence arrangements for the target SIL (SP-021).

Verification method: structured inspection by the Software Verifier (SP-021)
using a checklist derived from EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.2 requirements.

Checklist reference: <document ID or tool reference>
Verifier: <Name, Organisation, independence evidence>
<<<
